snippet: Dominique Strauss-Kahn and the hotel housekeeper who accused him of sexually assaulting her last year have agreed to settle her lawsuit stemming from their encounter.
abstract: Justice Douglas E McKeon of New York State Supreme Court in the Bronx announces settlement of civil lawsuit filed by Nafissatou Diallo against Dominique Strauss-Kahn in connection with incident in Midtown Manhattan hotel in May 2011; terms of settlement are not disclosed.
lead_paragraph: Dominique Strauss-Kahn and the hotel housekeeper who accused him of sexually assaulting her last year have agreed to settle her lawsuit stemming from their encounter.

headline.seo: Strauss-Kahn and Hotel Housekeeper Settle Suit Over Alleged Attack
headline.main: Hotel Worker Settles Claim Strauss-Kahn Forced Sex
headline.print_headline: Hotel Worker Settles Claim Strauss-Kahn Forced Sex
